WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.759 --> 00:00:13.179
DECEMBER 2020

2
00:00:14.264 --> 00:00:16.933
JINNAM BOXING

3
00:00:17.017 --> 00:00:19.019
[uptempo electronic music playing]

4
00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:27.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

5
00:00:29.237 --> 00:00:30.237
[exhales sharply]

6
00:00:33.199 --> 00:00:34.325
[exhales deeply]

7
00:00:36.953 --> 00:00:37.953
[exhales]

8
00:00:44.627 --> 00:00:45.962
[grunts]

9
00:01:03.271 --> 00:01:04.856
[grunts. exhales]

10
00:01:07.400 --> 00:01:10.737
- [coughing]
- [sirens wailing]

11
00:01:15.658 --> 00:01:16.658
[groans]

12
00:01:26.628 --> 00:01:28.463
[driver] Oh. uh. sir.

13
00:01:28.546 --> 00:01:31.257
- You need to wear a mask on the bus. sir.
- [man mumbling]

14
00:01:31.341 --> 00:01:33.635
[driver] You can't ride the bus
without a mask. I'm sorry.

15
00:01:33.718 --> 00:01:34.594
[man] Let's go.

16
00:01:34.677 --> 00:01:36.697
[driver] You'll be allowed on
when you return with a mask.

17
00:01:36.721 --> 00:01:38.473
Who are you to tell me what to do?
[shouts]

18
00:01:38.556 --> 00:01:40.934
- [driver] We get penalized...
- [man 1] What? A mask?

19
00:01:42.185 --> 00:01:44.229
- It's my choice!
- Please leave. sir.

20
00:01:44.813 --> 00:01:47.190
[man] You're a driver.
so drive the damn bus.

21
00:01:47.273 --> 00:01:48.274
[driver] I'm telling you.

22
00:01:48.358 --> 00:01:51.718
- Please put on a mask and come back. sir.
- [man 1] You're just a driver. Come here!

23
00:01:52.070 --> 00:01:54.340
- [driver] There are passengers on board.
- [man 2] Please don't do this.

24
00:01:54.364 --> 00:01:56.574
- [man 1] What the hell is this? Whoa!
- [man 2] Whoa!

25
00:01:56.658 --> 00:01:58.785
- Sorry. Sorry.
- [man 1] Get off of me.

26
00:01:59.577 --> 00:02:01.037
What? Who the hell are you?

27
00:02:01.121 --> 00:02:03.623
[man 2] I'm sorry. I think
you'll have to walk home. Sorry.

28
00:02:03.706 --> 00:02:05.208
- [man 1 grunts]
- I'm sorry.

29
00:02:05.291 --> 00:02:07.335
[groans] You shi...

30
00:02:07.418 --> 00:02:09.212
- [man 2] Sorry. sir.
- [grunts. winces]

31
00:02:09.295 --> 00:02:11.214
- [man 2] I'm very sorry.
- [grunts]

32
00:02:11.297 --> 00:02:12.590
[man 2] Whoa. I'm sorry.

33
00:02:12.674 --> 00:02:14.527
- I hope you're not hurt. Sorry. sir.
- [man 1 wincing]

34
00:02:14.551 --> 00:02:15.885
[groans]

35
00:02:17.762 --> 00:02:19.264
Goddamn you little...

36
00:02:19.848 --> 00:02:20.849
I'm very sorry.

37
00:02:22.100 --> 00:02:23.226
Bullshit.

38
00:02:24.769 --> 00:02:26.938
- I'm really sorry.
- My ass.

39
00:02:29.649 --> 00:02:30.649
[man 1 groans]

40
00:02:31.192 --> 00:02:33.027
[man 2] Sorry about that. Thank you.

41
00:02:33.111 --> 00:02:34.991
- [driver] Thank you. sir.
- [man 2] No problem.

42
00:02:36.948 --> 00:02:40.076
[driver] See.
the passengers are grateful too.

43
00:02:43.913 --> 00:02:45.331
[gentle piano music playing]

44
00:02:50.420 --> 00:02:51.420
[crosswalk beeping]

45
00:02:59.304 --> 00:03:01.222
[man] The guy in the mask kept saying...

46
00:03:13.776 --> 00:03:14.776
[exhales]

47
00:03:18.781 --> 00:03:19.908
[keys jingling]

48
00:03:21.951 --> 00:03:23.661
[woman] I'm so sorry.

49
00:03:24.162 --> 00:03:27.707
God. I had no idea it would go on
for this long. [whimpers]

50
00:03:28.917 --> 00:03:31.169
I am so sorry that I have to ask you.

51
00:03:31.252 --> 00:03:32.086
I'm sorry.

52
00:03:32.170 --> 00:03:34.756
I'll try to put something together
next month. I promise.

53
00:03:35.840 --> 00:03:39.928
So. do you think can you wait
just one more month?

54
00:03:41.095 --> 00:03:42.972
I... I promise I'll pay you back.

55
00:03:43.806 --> 00:03:46.726
Yes. yes. Next month. I'll try my best.

56
00:03:47.310 --> 00:03:48.645
Yes. thank you.

57
00:03:50.396 --> 00:03:51.648
[door latches]

58
00:03:54.651 --> 00:03:55.651
[sighs]

59
00:04:00.490 --> 00:04:02.492
[theme music playing]

60
00:04:27.016 --> 00:04:30.895
BLOODHOUNDS

61
00:04:33.898 --> 00:04:35.960
<i>Amidst the ongoing recession
brought on by COVID-19...</i>

62
00:04:35.984 --> 00:04:38.045
CITIZENS TREMBLE WITH ANXIETY
ABOUT ABANDONED BUILDINGS IN THE CITY

63
00:04:38.069 --> 00:04:41.131
<i>...a suspended building construction project
is threatening the safety of the citizens.</i>

64
00:04:41.155 --> 00:04:42.115
NO TRESPASSING

65
00:04:42.156 --> 00:04:44.718
<i>Construction on the building
you see behind me had been suspended twice</i>

66
00:04:44.742 --> 00:04:47.370
<i>due to on-site workers being diagnosed
with COVID-19.</i>

67
00:04:47.453 --> 00:04:49.640
<i>When the company went bankrupt.
the building was abandoned</i>

68
00:04:49.664 --> 00:04:51.582
<i>becoming an eyesore
in the middle of the city.</i>

69
00:04:51.666 --> 00:04:54.335
<i>Seoul City must act quickly
to resolve this situation.</i>

70
00:04:54.836 --> 00:04:56.421
[gentle piano music playing]

71
00:05:02.051 --> 00:05:05.179
In the United States. over 3.5 million
hotel employees were laid off

72
00:05:05.263 --> 00:05:06.681
in the third quarter alone.

73
00:05:06.764 --> 00:05:08.808
I'm telling you
that for the next three to for years

74
00:05:08.891 --> 00:05:12.103
there will be no foreign companies
interested in acquiring this hotel.

75
00:05:12.603 --> 00:05:13.883
Domestic companies even less so.

76
00:05:13.938 --> 00:05:15.857
You make these claims
as though they're facts.

77
00:05:15.940 --> 00:05:17.817
I have a lot of friends
who are future leaders

78
00:05:17.900 --> 00:05:19.652
of Korea's top fifty corporations.

79
00:05:19.736 --> 00:05:22.423
I have thoroughly discussed it with them
and reached this conclusion.

80
00:05:22.447 --> 00:05:24.449
so these claims are highly likely
to be factual.

81
00:05:25.325 --> 00:05:26.325
Actually.

82
00:05:27.201 --> 00:05:28.536
they are simply facts.

83
00:05:29.245 --> 00:05:31.956
You'd be doing well to negotiate with me.
Mr. Vice President.

84
00:05:32.040 --> 00:05:33.040
Mr. Hong.

85
00:05:34.042 --> 00:05:37.628
As you know. our bank has already lent
400 billion won to this building.

86
00:05:37.712 --> 00:05:40.131
Stating you will only be paying back
300 isn't a negotiation.

87
00:05:40.214 --> 00:05:43.176
Shouldn't one be prepared to accept
some losses in the current situation?

88
00:05:43.760 --> 00:05:45.053
How else can business be done?

89
00:05:45.678 --> 00:05:48.681
I am not a businessman.
but I am the banker.

90
00:05:49.307 --> 00:05:51.809
Uh. Mr. Director. Mr. Vice President.

91
00:05:51.893 --> 00:05:53.811
the reason I brought the two of you
over here...

92
00:05:53.895 --> 00:05:54.729
[director] Yes.

93
00:05:54.812 --> 00:05:58.024
...is to push for a speedy completion
of the construction work on the building

94
00:05:58.107 --> 00:05:59.400
for the citizens' safety.

95
00:05:59.484 --> 00:06:01.361
Talking to him
is like talking to a brick wall.

96
00:06:01.444 --> 00:06:04.030
If you're suggesting
that I'm being unreasonable.

97
00:06:04.113 --> 00:06:06.699
let me ask you this.
which part of what you said is reasonable?

98
00:06:15.625 --> 00:06:17.710
I must apologize for my tardiness.

99
00:06:18.544 --> 00:06:21.714
This is Mr. Kim Myeong-gil.
I mentioned him before our meal.

100
00:06:22.215 --> 00:06:23.257
May I introduce you.

101
00:06:23.341 --> 00:06:26.344
Assemblyman Seo Woo-hyeon.
a close acquaintance of the mayor.

102
00:06:26.928 --> 00:06:28.596
introduced him to us.

103
00:06:29.430 --> 00:06:30.598
Kim Myeong-gil.

104
00:06:32.767 --> 00:06:34.852
KIM MYEONG-GIL

105
00:06:34.936 --> 00:06:35.770
[inhales]

106
00:06:35.853 --> 00:06:37.814
I'll contact you individually later today.

107
00:06:38.439 --> 00:06:39.439
Okay.

108
00:06:43.986 --> 00:06:44.986
Kim Myeong-gil.

109
00:06:55.748 --> 00:06:58.126
Excuse me.
but what kind of work do you do?

110
00:06:59.127 --> 00:07:00.878
Primarily I deal with investments.

111
00:07:00.962 --> 00:07:03.172
When good people request my assistance.

112
00:07:03.256 --> 00:07:05.550
I help them out
to the best of my abilities.

113
00:07:05.633 --> 00:07:08.052
So are you a moneylender?

114
00:07:08.136 --> 00:07:09.011
[chuckles]

115
00:07:09.095 --> 00:07:12.223
Hey. did you know
that this man's a loan shark?

116
00:07:13.099 --> 00:07:15.476
Mr. Kim dabbles in various lines of work.

117
00:07:15.560 --> 00:07:18.080
You really think this is the right place
to bring this predator?

118
00:07:20.398 --> 00:07:23.109
And you must be the eldest son
of Chairman Hong Woo-geun.

119
00:07:24.444 --> 00:07:27.447
When I was young. I worked for someone
named Chairman Bang in Myeong-dong.

120
00:07:28.239 --> 00:07:30.575
You wouldn't remember
since you were a baby at that time.

121
00:07:30.658 --> 00:07:32.785
but when the IMF crisis hit Korea.

122
00:07:32.869 --> 00:07:35.872
Iil Group nearly went bankrupt
because they didn't have six billion

123
00:07:35.955 --> 00:07:37.457
after fifty years in business.

124
00:07:37.999 --> 00:07:41.836
Back then. Chairman Hong Woo-geun
went to my boss. Chairman Bang.

125
00:07:41.919 --> 00:07:43.463
to ask for assistance.

126
00:07:43.546 --> 00:07:46.007
He got down on his knees
saying he had to save the company

127
00:07:46.090 --> 00:07:47.091
at whatever cost.

128
00:07:47.633 --> 00:07:50.678
And with all his sincerity
and his passion.

129
00:07:50.761 --> 00:07:51.762
he got to Chairman Bang.

130
00:07:53.097 --> 00:07:54.097
So then.

131
00:07:54.515 --> 00:07:56.601
I filled up a bag
with six billion in cash.

132
00:07:56.684 --> 00:07:57.884
and I went over to your house.

133
00:07:58.644 --> 00:08:02.482
I also remember your mother prepared
some refreshing Korean melon for me

134
00:08:02.565 --> 00:08:03.733
to express her gratitude.

135
00:08:05.067 --> 00:08:08.070
There is no dirty money
unless it's used for nefarious agendas.

136
00:08:08.154 --> 00:08:10.740
but when used for good.
that makes it good money.

137
00:08:11.324 --> 00:08:14.202
I came here
to extend what support I have to offer.

138
00:08:17.955 --> 00:08:20.458
How are the negotiations?

139
00:08:21.125 --> 00:08:23.878
There were differences
in the amount they had in mind.

140
00:08:23.961 --> 00:08:27.215
- So we were just talking.
- Ah... How much of discrepancy?

141
00:08:27.298 --> 00:08:28.466
A hundred billion.

142
00:08:28.966 --> 00:08:29.966
[scoffs]

143
00:08:32.678 --> 00:08:36.599
Mr. Hong. do you plan on overseeing
hotel operations yourself?

144
00:08:36.682 --> 00:08:39.435
I got my master's in hotel management
in Switzerland

145
00:08:39.936 --> 00:08:41.496
and worked for four years in Hong Kong.

146
00:08:41.521 --> 00:08:43.648
I see you are well-prepared.

147
00:08:45.233 --> 00:08:48.444
With your permission.
I would like to make an investment.

148
00:08:48.528 --> 00:08:51.239
[inhales deeply] What's your offer?

149
00:08:51.322 --> 00:08:55.785
Well... you need 100 billion.
so I'll invest that much.

150
00:08:59.330 --> 00:09:02.124
If need be. I will invest more.

151
00:09:02.208 --> 00:09:03.208
What are the terms?

152
00:09:03.251 --> 00:09:04.251
Right.

153
00:09:04.627 --> 00:09:05.920
There are only three.

154
00:09:06.462 --> 00:09:09.423
First off.
I would like to have a small casino

155
00:09:09.924 --> 00:09:12.176
built on the highest floor
of the hotel's structure.

156
00:09:12.260 --> 00:09:14.804
Just as you dream of managing a hotel.
Mr. Hong.

157
00:09:14.887 --> 00:09:17.431
well. I dream of operating my own casino.

158
00:09:18.432 --> 00:09:19.559
And secondly.

159
00:09:19.642 --> 00:09:23.563
I ask that you help me set up a small bar
in the basement of the hotel.

160
00:09:23.646 --> 00:09:25.231
The last thing is.

161
00:09:25.314 --> 00:09:27.358
if something like COVID-19
were to spread again.

162
00:09:27.441 --> 00:09:30.820
I would like our hotel
to be a quarantine space.

163
00:09:30.903 --> 00:09:33.614
for those without money.
and it will be free of charge.

164
00:09:34.490 --> 00:09:35.741
The harder the times get.

165
00:09:35.825 --> 00:09:38.494
the more we all should be looking out
for one another.

166
00:09:38.578 --> 00:09:41.747
Because... that's how we build
a better world.

167
00:09:46.043 --> 00:09:47.712
The 100 billion won investment

168
00:09:48.504 --> 00:09:50.715
can be available to you
as early as tomorrow.

169
00:09:52.008 --> 00:09:53.509
[ominous music playing]

170
00:10:06.689 --> 00:10:08.566
- [grunts]
- It went well?

171
00:10:09.984 --> 00:10:11.819
- Mm-hm.
- So they'll bite?

172
00:10:12.403 --> 00:10:15.740
- [scoffs] Mm.
- [laughs]

173
00:10:16.324 --> 00:10:17.158
[woman] Oh yay!

174
00:10:17.241 --> 00:10:20.286
So I guess I need to start thinking
about how I want to decorate the bar!

175
00:10:20.369 --> 00:10:22.913
Well. uh. people don't go to bars
to see how they're decorated.

176
00:10:22.997 --> 00:10:24.540
They go to see the girls.

177
00:10:24.624 --> 00:10:26.504
So you better get busy
hiring some pretty girls.

178
00:10:27.043 --> 00:10:29.128
No. I think you should get busy.
you fucker.

179
00:10:29.211 --> 00:10:32.214
You know. it would be better
if you could talk as nice as you look.

180
00:10:32.298 --> 00:10:34.133
What would you know? You prick!

181
00:10:34.634 --> 00:10:35.468
[exhales forcefully]

182
00:10:35.551 --> 00:10:37.053
- [woman laughs]
- [scoffs]

183
00:10:37.637 --> 00:10:39.013
I need to wipe my face.

184
00:10:39.597 --> 00:10:40.597
Oh.

185
00:10:41.766 --> 00:10:42.846
[Myeong-gil exhales deeply]

186
00:10:43.392 --> 00:10:44.392
Here you go.

187
00:10:49.315 --> 00:10:51.108
[ominous music playing]

188
00:10:59.742 --> 00:11:00.785
Let's get going.

189
00:11:05.206 --> 00:11:06.707
How's the Seongeun Building?

190
00:11:06.791 --> 00:11:10.002
None of the tenants have any ties
to the police or prosecutor's office.

191
00:11:10.086 --> 00:11:11.379
Did you also check in-laws?

192
00:11:11.462 --> 00:11:14.131
Yes. of course. I told you
I only overlooked it that one time.

193
00:11:14.215 --> 00:11:16.300
Someone could have a partner who's a cop.

194
00:11:16.801 --> 00:11:18.561
Do your job well
so he doesn't have to worry.

195
00:11:18.636 --> 00:11:20.513
Ah. why don't you worry about yourself?

196
00:11:21.013 --> 00:11:22.098
Jang-do.

197
00:11:23.265 --> 00:11:25.601
you should speak to my woman
with more respect.

198
00:11:26.894 --> 00:11:28.604
Yes. you're right. I'm sorry. sir.

199
00:11:28.688 --> 00:11:30.606
Hey. apologize to me. you asshole.

200
00:11:30.690 --> 00:11:31.565
[inhales sharply]

201
00:11:31.649 --> 00:11:33.734
This asshole apologizes to you. ma'am.

202
00:11:33.818 --> 00:11:36.487
[groans] Hurry up. please.
I could really use a drink.

203
00:11:36.570 --> 00:11:37.570
[Jang-do] Yes. sir.

204
00:11:39.865 --> 00:11:42.827
[commentator 1] This is the 2020 KBFC
Rookie of the Year Tournament.

205
00:11:42.910 --> 00:11:44.846
The Rookie of the Year Tournament
is supposed to be held

206
00:11:44.870 --> 00:11:48.290
amidst the loud shouting and cheering
of fans expressing their love and support.

207
00:11:48.374 --> 00:11:50.501
but due to COVID-19.
there are no spectators today.

208
00:11:50.584 --> 00:11:52.464
It feels rather gloomy in here.
don't you think?

209
00:11:52.503 --> 00:11:53.337
That's right.

210
00:11:53.421 --> 00:11:55.607
The Rookie of the Year tournament
is normally a rowdy affair

211
00:11:55.631 --> 00:11:56.900
with lots of cheering for everyone.

212
00:11:56.924 --> 00:11:58.193
- [coaches yelling]
- [bell dings]

213
00:11:58.217 --> 00:12:01.303
[commentator 1] <i>As we speak. we begin
the third round of Hong Woo-jin's match.</i>

214
00:12:01.387 --> 00:12:02.972
<i>Now we have a middleweight match here</i>

215
00:12:03.055 --> 00:12:04.598
<i>with Hong Woo-jin in the red trunks.</i>

216
00:12:04.682 --> 00:12:06.684
<i>going up against Jung Jae-hun
in the blue trunks.</i>

217
00:12:06.767 --> 00:12:07.601
[coach 1] Get in there.

218
00:12:07.685 --> 00:12:09.565
[commentator 2]
<i>Great combination of body shots.</i>

219
00:12:09.645 --> 00:12:11.957
[commentator 1] <i>Now we see Hong Woo-jin
leaning against the ropes.</i>

220
00:12:11.981 --> 00:12:14.042
[commentator 2] <i>He provokes his opponent
after landing body shots.</i>

221
00:12:14.066 --> 00:12:16.277
[commentator 1]
<i>Would you look at that provocation.</i>

222
00:12:16.360 --> 00:12:18.446
<i>I mean. I wouldn't go near.</i>

223
00:12:18.529 --> 00:12:20.239
<i>Whoa. a body shot!</i>

224
00:12:20.322 --> 00:12:22.509
- [coach cheers]
- [commentator 2] <i>A clean hit to the body.</i>

225
00:12:22.533 --> 00:12:24.293
[commentator 1]
<i>He landed a blow to the face.</i>

226
00:12:24.368 --> 00:12:26.537
<i>He knocks his opponent down! Hong Woo-jin!</i>

227
00:12:26.620 --> 00:12:29.099
[commentator 2] <i>Whoa! A double right
followed by a one-two strike.</i>

228
00:12:29.123 --> 00:12:31.959
[commentator 1] <i>Look at that footwork.
He has great showmanship.</i>

229
00:12:32.042 --> 00:12:33.322
[commentator 2] <i>Whoa. it's a KO.</i>

230
00:12:33.836 --> 00:12:34.836
KIM RAE-HYEON
KIM GUN-WOO

231
00:12:34.879 --> 00:12:37.519
[commentator 1] <i>We have Kim Gun-woo
going up against Kim Rae-hyeon.</i>

232
00:12:37.548 --> 00:12:40.068
<i>Kim Gun-woo in blue. everybody.
the super rookie in blue trunks.</i>

233
00:12:40.134 --> 00:12:43.512
[commentator 2] <i>Kim Gun-woo is looking
for a chance with his guard up.</i>

234
00:12:43.596 --> 00:12:45.615
<i>- A body blow!</i>
- [commentator 1] <i>He goes to his knees!</i>

235
00:12:45.639 --> 00:12:48.201
[commentator 2] <i>That's right.
A precision blow to the solar plexus...</i>

236
00:12:48.225 --> 00:12:50.245
<i>- That's the end of the match.</i>
- [commentator 2] <i>Indeed.</i>

237
00:12:50.269 --> 00:12:52.062
[commentator 1] <i>Ending with just one blow.</i>

238
00:12:52.146 --> 00:12:54.940
<i>Kim Gun-woo mows down his opponent
with a single blow again.</i>

239
00:12:55.024 --> 00:12:56.543
[commentator 2]
<i>He's a matchless competitor.</i>

240
00:12:56.567 --> 00:12:58.128
[commentator 1]
<i>A terrifying rookie has emerged.</i>

241
00:12:58.152 --> 00:13:00.446
[commentator 2]
<i>Things are already getting heated.</i>

242
00:13:00.529 --> 00:13:02.281
[commentator 1] <i>He's getting cornered.</i>

243
00:13:02.364 --> 00:13:05.159
[coaches shouting indistinctly]

244
00:13:05.242 --> 00:13:08.245
<i>He grabs him and throws him over.
He threw his opponent down.</i>

245
00:13:08.329 --> 00:13:09.931
[commentator 2]
<i>That was against the rules.</i>

246
00:13:09.955 --> 00:13:13.375
- He did it first.
- [commentator 2] <i>He's too agitated now.</i>

247
00:13:13.459 --> 00:13:15.461
- [referee] Box!
- [man] Let's do this!

248
00:13:15.544 --> 00:13:18.297
[commentator 1] <i>He parts his hair.
Hong's showmanship is unmatched.</i>

249
00:13:18.380 --> 00:13:20.257
[commentator 2]
That is Hong Woo-jin for you.

250
00:13:20.341 --> 00:13:21.901
[commentator 1] <i>He provokes. He dodges.</i>

251
00:13:21.967 --> 00:13:23.260
<i>Wow! Look at him dodge!</i>

252
00:13:23.761 --> 00:13:25.054
[boxers grunting]

253
00:13:25.721 --> 00:13:28.682
<i>Here he goes again...
He connects! We have a knockdown!</i>

254
00:13:28.766 --> 00:13:30.566
[commentator 2]
<i>It's Hong Woo-jin's specialty.</i>

255
00:13:30.601 --> 00:13:32.144
<i>A double jab followed by a straight!</i>

256
00:13:32.228 --> 00:13:33.979
[commentator 1] <i>Hong Woo-jin. the marine.</i>

257
00:13:34.063 --> 00:13:35.272
<i>Hong Woo-jin advances again.</i>

258
00:13:35.356 --> 00:13:36.398
HONG WOO-JIN

259
00:13:36.482 --> 00:13:37.501
[Gun-woo's coach] Go lower.

260
00:13:37.525 --> 00:13:39.920
[commentator 1] <i>A match between
Kim Gun-woo and Lee Yong-gyu.</i>

261
00:13:39.944 --> 00:13:41.529
[boxers grunting]

262
00:13:41.612 --> 00:13:44.365
<i>Kim Gun-woo in the red trunks
is built like a tank.</i>

263
00:13:44.448 --> 00:13:45.783
<i>He dodges both blows.</i>

264
00:13:45.866 --> 00:13:48.452
[commentator 2]
<i>Kim Gun-woo's strength lies in infighting.</i>

265
00:13:48.536 --> 00:13:51.372
<i>He is leveraging his skills
in close-range hitting.</i>

266
00:13:51.455 --> 00:13:53.541
[commentator 1]
<i>Another punch. and he dodges.</i>

267
00:13:53.624 --> 00:13:57.461
<i>A body shot! He brings down his opponent
with one blow!</i>

268
00:13:57.545 --> 00:13:59.145
[commentator 2] <i>A left hook to the body.</i>

269
00:13:59.171 --> 00:14:01.382
<i>I had that level of talent
when I was a contender.</i>

270
00:14:01.465 --> 00:14:03.551
- [Gun-woo] Are you all right?
- Yeah.

271
00:14:03.634 --> 00:14:06.053
[commentator 1]
<i>That's why you won a gold medal.</i>

272
00:14:06.804 --> 00:14:08.514
<i>Now. Kim Gun-woo versus Hong Woo-jin.</i>

273
00:14:08.597 --> 00:14:11.267
- Yeah. let's see.
- Let's find out who takes home the trophy.

274
00:14:11.350 --> 00:14:14.019
No big moves.
Short punches. Use your waist!

275
00:14:14.103 --> 00:14:16.856
Watch out for his left hook.
His punches are no joke.

276
00:14:23.737 --> 00:14:26.240
Bro. I'm a marine.

277
00:14:26.323 --> 00:14:27.157
THE STRONGEST

278
00:14:27.241 --> 00:14:28.492
Watch out for his left hook.

279
00:14:28.576 --> 00:14:30.911
And I'm telling you.
I'm an invincible marine.

280
00:14:30.995 --> 00:14:34.081
Okay. but don't cry
if you get the shit beat out of you.

281
00:14:34.164 --> 00:14:35.164
All right?

282
00:14:35.541 --> 00:14:36.541
[exhales deeply]

283
00:14:39.044 --> 00:14:40.884
- [coach 1] Let's go!
- [coach 2] You got this.

284
00:14:40.921 --> 00:14:41.755
Keep your hands up.

285
00:14:41.839 --> 00:14:43.559
- [referee] Come forward to meet.
- [grunts]

286
00:14:43.632 --> 00:14:45.801
Now good luck to you both.
To your corners.

287
00:14:49.972 --> 00:14:52.534
[commentator 1] <i>His fighting up until now
has truly been a marvel.</i>

288
00:14:52.558 --> 00:14:55.686
<i>Kim Gun-woo. the super rookie.
has a very unique fighting style.</i>

289
00:14:55.769 --> 00:14:57.956
[commentator 2] <i>That's right.
Kim Gun-woo is an infighter</i>

290
00:14:57.980 --> 00:14:59.460
<i>that's good against other infighters.</i>

291
00:14:59.523 --> 00:15:00.983
[commentator 1] <i>Right.</i>

292
00:15:01.066 --> 00:15:02.252
[commentator 2] <i>On the other hand.</i>

293
00:15:02.276 --> 00:15:05.654
<i>Hong Woo-jin is an out-boxer
with a counter up his sleeve.</i>

294
00:15:05.738 --> 00:15:08.008
[commentator 1] <i>That's right.
Hong Woo-jin knows how to have fun</i>

295
00:15:08.032 --> 00:15:09.116
<i>during his matches.</i>

296
00:15:09.199 --> 00:15:10.468
[commentator 1] <i>On the other hand.</i>

297
00:15:10.492 --> 00:15:13.037
<i>we have his opponent
who stoically plays it by the book.</i>

298
00:15:13.120 --> 00:15:15.831
<i>He's going in! He's going!
He's cornering him!</i>

299
00:15:15.915 --> 00:15:18.500
<i>Can Hong Woo-jin get out?
Can he get out of this?</i>

300
00:15:18.584 --> 00:15:20.669
<i>Wow! He got out of that really well.</i>

301
00:15:20.753 --> 00:15:23.547
[commentator 2]
<i>Hong Woo-jin is just remarkably fast.</i>

302
00:15:23.631 --> 00:15:26.425
<i>And since Kim Gun-woo
is also a middleweight...</i>

303
00:15:26.508 --> 00:15:28.636
[commentator 1] <i>Wow.
he goes for a wild swing!</i>

304
00:15:28.719 --> 00:15:31.055
<i>Here we go. He guards the body shot.</i>

305
00:15:31.138 --> 00:15:33.018
[commentator 2]
<i>Kim Gun-woo has a great defense.</i>

306
00:15:33.098 --> 00:15:35.410
- [commentator 1] <i>Doesn't he?</i>
- [commentator 2] <i>He's like a rock.</i>

307
00:15:35.434 --> 00:15:36.936
<i>And he keeps on guarding.</i>

308
00:15:37.019 --> 00:15:38.747
- [both grunting]
- [commentator 1] <i>Uppercut!</i>

309
00:15:38.771 --> 00:15:40.481
<i>He landed that one.</i>

310
00:15:40.564 --> 00:15:41.774
[commentator 2] <i>Indeed he did.</i>

311
00:15:41.857 --> 00:15:43.537
[commentator 1]
<i>What a performance this is.</i>

312
00:15:43.567 --> 00:15:45.945
<i>A right hook! Wow. what a dodge.</i>

313
00:15:46.028 --> 00:15:46.862
[Woo-jin grunting]

314
00:15:46.946 --> 00:15:50.074
<i>Hong Woo-jin is
constantly applying nonstop pressure.</i>

315
00:15:50.908 --> 00:15:53.386
- [commentator 2] <i>Another left.</i>
- [commentator 1] <i>Can he recover?</i>

316
00:15:53.410 --> 00:15:55.371
<i>And Hong Woo-jin... He goes down.</i>

317
00:15:55.454 --> 00:15:57.623
<i>- He's down!</i>
- One... two...

318
00:15:57.706 --> 00:15:59.684
<i>- Three... four</i>
- [commentator 2] <i>With stomach blows.</i>

319
00:15:59.708 --> 00:16:01.108
<i>the shock does not come right away.</i>

320
00:16:01.168 --> 00:16:04.213
<i>It takes around five seconds.
That is when it hits.</i>

321
00:16:04.296 --> 00:16:06.256
- [Woo-jin groans]
- [referee] Six. seven...

322
00:16:06.340 --> 00:16:08.140
[commentator 1] He gets up
after five seconds.

323
00:16:08.175 --> 00:16:09.802
<i>He recovered well from that one.</i>

324
00:16:09.885 --> 00:16:10.803
<i>Yes. he did.</i>

325
00:16:10.886 --> 00:16:12.966
[commentator 2]
<i>But that has definitely got to sting.</i>

326
00:16:13.013 --> 00:16:15.307
[commentator 1]
<i>There's going to be an aftereffect.</i>

327
00:16:15.391 --> 00:16:16.471
[commentator 2] I think so.

328
00:16:17.226 --> 00:16:18.060
Come on.

329
00:16:18.143 --> 00:16:20.062
[rock music playing]

330
00:16:20.145 --> 00:16:23.565
Come on!

331
00:16:28.195 --> 00:16:29.279
[Woo-jin grunts]

332
00:16:30.197 --> 00:16:32.074
[music fades]

333
00:16:36.120 --> 00:16:36.996
[rock music resumes]

334
00:16:37.079 --> 00:16:40.040
[yelling]

335
00:16:41.583 --> 00:16:42.583
[exhales deeply]

336
00:16:48.173 --> 00:16:49.173
Come on.

337
00:16:49.717 --> 00:16:52.052
Hey... come get some.

338
00:16:53.721 --> 00:16:54.888
Son of a bitch.

339
00:16:57.891 --> 00:16:59.893
Come get me!

340
00:17:01.603 --> 00:17:03.123
[commentator 1] <i>Will he take the bait?</i>

341
00:17:03.188 --> 00:17:05.357
<i>- Kim Gun-woo has a lot to think about.</i>
- Come on!

342
00:17:05.441 --> 00:17:07.735
[commentator 1]
<i>And there he goes! Will he connect?</i>

343
00:17:07.818 --> 00:17:11.155
- Stop! One. two...
- [Woo-jin groaning]

344
00:17:11.238 --> 00:17:13.574
- Three... four...
- [Woo-jin whimpering]

345
00:17:13.657 --> 00:17:15.417
[commentator 1]
<i>His tactics really backfired.</i>

346
00:17:15.492 --> 00:17:16.326
[referee] KO!

347
00:17:16.410 --> 00:17:18.138
[commentator 1]
<i>Kim Gun-woo went in for the kill</i>

348
00:17:18.162 --> 00:17:21.790
<i>and ended the match
once again with the same body shot.</i>

349
00:17:21.874 --> 00:17:24.293
<i>I'll tell you something.
That body shot is ruthless.</i>

350
00:17:24.376 --> 00:17:26.587
- [sighs]
- [Woo-jin whimpering]

351
00:17:28.464 --> 00:17:29.590
You all right?

352
00:17:30.424 --> 00:17:32.843
I have tainted the honor
of my fellow marines.

353
00:17:33.427 --> 00:17:35.095
A blow to the liver will do that.

354
00:17:36.430 --> 00:17:37.639
Okay. I'm out of here.

355
00:17:38.474 --> 00:17:39.892
What about dinner. huh?

356
00:17:40.601 --> 00:17:41.810
There's the pandemic.

357
00:17:42.394 --> 00:17:44.154
I mean.
your boy has just gone through a lot.

358
00:17:44.188 --> 00:17:45.564
The least you can do is feed him.

359
00:18:01.455 --> 00:18:02.915
Go home and order in.

360
00:18:04.708 --> 00:18:05.708
[sighs]

361
00:18:06.126 --> 00:18:07.126
Later.

362
00:18:11.131 --> 00:18:12.674
[wincing]

363
00:18:16.303 --> 00:18:17.513
[exhales]

364
00:18:19.098 --> 00:18:20.098
Oh.

365
00:18:23.227 --> 00:18:24.853
What? Huh? What?

366
00:18:25.854 --> 00:18:26.855
Wanna grab a bite?

367
00:18:27.606 --> 00:18:29.274
Why would I wanna grab food with you?

368
00:18:29.858 --> 00:18:32.277
I was gonna get some pork belly.
Thought you might want some.

369
00:18:34.655 --> 00:18:35.531
[inhales sharply]

370
00:18:35.614 --> 00:18:36.614
Are you pitying me?

371
00:18:37.157 --> 00:18:37.991
No.

372
00:18:38.075 --> 00:18:40.202
Go ask those other assholes you KO'd
to eat with you.

373
00:18:40.285 --> 00:18:41.912
But they all went home.

374
00:18:43.122 --> 00:18:44.248
[sighs]

375
00:18:56.677 --> 00:18:58.804
- Wasn't the prize money ten million?
- Yeah.

376
00:19:00.264 --> 00:19:02.057
Then why settle for pork belly?

377
00:19:02.141 --> 00:19:03.392
Let's get rib eye.

378
00:19:03.475 --> 00:19:06.145
- I'm only going to spend 50.000.
- Why?

379
00:19:06.228 --> 00:19:07.980
I need to give the rest to my mom.

380
00:19:08.063 --> 00:19:10.107
- Do you owe your mom money?
- No.

381
00:19:10.190 --> 00:19:11.190
Then why?

382
00:19:11.567 --> 00:19:13.443
I have to pay the rent for her store.

383
00:19:14.319 --> 00:19:15.404
You're a good son.

384
00:19:16.196 --> 00:19:17.614
Just spend an extra 10.000.

385
00:19:17.698 --> 00:19:20.284
This barbecue buffet I know
charges 29.000 a person.

386
00:19:20.367 --> 00:19:22.035
It's insane. and they serve Korean beef.

387
00:19:22.119 --> 00:19:23.954
- You serious?
- Of course not. idiot.

388
00:19:24.454 --> 00:19:25.455
[Woo-jin scoffs]

389
00:19:25.539 --> 00:19:28.500
How could they afford
to serve Korean beef that cheap? [scoffs]

390
00:19:28.584 --> 00:19:30.377
Do you spend all your time working out?

391
00:19:31.461 --> 00:19:33.881
Anyway. that buffet is all right.
Just spend a little more.

392
00:19:33.964 --> 00:19:34.964
No.

393
00:19:35.924 --> 00:19:36.924
[sighs]

394
00:19:37.259 --> 00:19:38.259
Hey.

395
00:19:46.435 --> 00:19:47.978
[gentle instrumental music playing]

396
00:19:48.061 --> 00:19:49.061
Let's go.

397
00:19:50.480 --> 00:19:52.107
How is your left hook so strong?

398
00:19:52.983 --> 00:19:54.663
Back when I worked part-time
at a junkyard.

399
00:19:54.693 --> 00:19:56.028
I practiced my hooks on a tire.

400
00:19:56.111 --> 00:19:57.279
Just your left?

401
00:19:58.405 --> 00:19:59.781
Why would I only work on my left?

402
00:19:59.865 --> 00:20:01.867
No. I'm asking
if you only worked on your left.

403
00:20:01.950 --> 00:20:03.785
No. of course I hit with both hands.

404
00:20:03.869 --> 00:20:05.537
Then why is your left so strong?

405
00:20:05.621 --> 00:20:08.874
- Actually. my right is stronger.
- Then why use only your left?

406
00:20:08.957 --> 00:20:11.293
Because I couldn't find a good time
to use my right.

407
00:20:12.628 --> 00:20:13.628
What a show-off.

408
00:20:14.588 --> 00:20:15.422
You think so?

409
00:20:15.505 --> 00:20:17.985
You're saying you could take
everyone down with just your left.

410
00:20:18.258 --> 00:20:19.468
At least today. yes.

411
00:20:19.551 --> 00:20:21.386
Yeah. see? What a show-off.

412
00:20:21.970 --> 00:20:23.370
Actually. I consider myself humble.

413
00:20:23.430 --> 00:20:24.306
Flip the pork already.

414
00:20:24.389 --> 00:20:26.308
Not yet. It needs 30 more seconds.

415
00:20:26.391 --> 00:20:28.143
Well. I think it's ready now.

416
00:20:28.227 --> 00:20:30.288
You're wrong.
I worked part-time at a barbecue place.

417
00:20:30.312 --> 00:20:31.355
I know my meat.

418
00:20:31.438 --> 00:20:34.024
Damn. bro.
you've worked a lot of part-time jobs.

419
00:20:34.107 --> 00:20:35.525
- Are you poor?
- Mm-hm.

420
00:20:35.609 --> 00:20:37.069
My family lost everything.

421
00:20:39.488 --> 00:20:40.488
How?

422
00:20:41.490 --> 00:20:42.490
[clicks tongue]

423
00:20:42.866 --> 00:20:45.244
My dad was a researcher
for a large corporation.

424
00:20:45.327 --> 00:20:47.931
He sued them for wrongful termination
and ended up losing the suit.

425
00:20:47.955 --> 00:20:48.789
[sighs]

426
00:20:48.872 --> 00:20:51.250
Legal fees from back then all became debt.

427
00:20:52.251 --> 00:20:54.812
You can't beat the big companies.
The rich always come out on top.

428
00:20:54.836 --> 00:20:55.879
That's true.

429
00:20:58.590 --> 00:21:01.551
- What were your other gigs?
- Well. I dabbled in this and that.

430
00:21:01.635 --> 00:21:03.555
For the most part.
I made deliveries with my mom.

431
00:21:03.637 --> 00:21:04.638
[scoffs]

432
00:21:04.721 --> 00:21:06.321
I guess you're a world-class part-timer.

433
00:21:07.432 --> 00:21:08.432
[chuckles]

434
00:21:09.101 --> 00:21:10.435
Oh!

435
00:21:10.519 --> 00:21:13.021
You are good at everything.
You've led a good life.

436
00:21:13.563 --> 00:21:15.107
I see you grill with your right hand.

437
00:21:15.190 --> 00:21:16.190
[chuckles]

438
00:21:16.233 --> 00:21:17.567
So when did you start boxing?

439
00:21:18.277 --> 00:21:20.195
Uh. about three years ago.

440
00:21:20.279 --> 00:21:22.281
- After school?
- After my military service.

441
00:21:22.364 --> 00:21:23.532
Ah... [inhales sharply]

442
00:21:24.032 --> 00:21:26.344
I first put on my gloves
for the first time in sixth grade.

443
00:21:26.368 --> 00:21:27.995
My dad was on the national team.

444
00:21:28.078 --> 00:21:30.122
Wow. that's so cool.

445
00:21:30.205 --> 00:21:31.540
And so what's your father's name?

446
00:21:31.623 --> 00:21:32.623
Hong Seong-geun.

447
00:21:33.125 --> 00:21:34.501
Barcelona bronze medalist.

448
00:21:34.584 --> 00:21:36.169
- Oh.
- Know him?

449
00:21:36.253 --> 00:21:37.379
No.

450
00:21:38.463 --> 00:21:40.048
Most boxers seem to know him.

451
00:21:40.132 --> 00:21:42.134
Oh. Sorry.

452
00:21:43.593 --> 00:21:45.433
I assume
your dad taught you how to box. right?

453
00:21:46.138 --> 00:21:47.222
We aren't that close.

454
00:21:48.098 --> 00:21:49.098
Why?

455
00:21:49.433 --> 00:21:51.435
My dad is never satisfied
with anything that I do.

456
00:21:52.269 --> 00:21:54.062
He won his bronze medal at my age.

457
00:21:54.896 --> 00:21:57.107
so he judges me
based on his accomplishments.

458
00:21:57.607 --> 00:21:58.775
Hm. [clicks tongue]

459
00:21:59.526 --> 00:22:01.028
So you're basically saying

460
00:22:01.528 --> 00:22:03.408
that your dad won a bronze medal
at the Olympics

461
00:22:03.447 --> 00:22:05.007
when he was only twenty-five years old?

462
00:22:06.074 --> 00:22:07.617
No. twenty-seven.

463
00:22:10.746 --> 00:22:12.247
Oh. how old are you?

464
00:22:12.831 --> 00:22:14.041
Twenty-seven.

465
00:22:14.124 --> 00:22:15.208
[inhales sharply] Uh.

466
00:22:15.834 --> 00:22:18.938
I'm sorry. man. I'm actually twenty-five.
I'm sorry. Please forgive my manners.

467
00:22:18.962 --> 00:22:20.756
Ah. you ass!

468
00:22:20.839 --> 00:22:21.673
Please forgive me.

469
00:22:21.757 --> 00:22:22.799
- Hey.
- Yes?

470
00:22:22.883 --> 00:22:24.593
Learn to respect your elders. got it?

471
00:22:24.676 --> 00:22:25.927
- Yes.
- Understand?

472
00:22:26.470 --> 00:22:27.470
Sure.

473
00:22:27.971 --> 00:22:28.889
Flip it now.

474
00:22:28.972 --> 00:22:31.266
Oh. not yet.
It still needs one more minute.

475
00:22:31.350 --> 00:22:33.518
- I said to flip it.
- I can't do that.

476
00:22:33.602 --> 00:22:37.147
Oh god. you are one stubborn punk. bro.
You've served in the army?

477
00:22:37.230 --> 00:22:40.251
Yes. I told you earlier I started boxing
after I finished my military service.

478
00:22:40.275 --> 00:22:41.568
Yeah. you did.

479
00:22:41.651 --> 00:22:43.737
What I mean is.
where were you stationed. huh?

480
00:22:43.820 --> 00:22:45.131
- Oh.
- You need to learn to keep up.

481
00:22:45.155 --> 00:22:47.240
Um. yes. I was in the Marine Corps.

482
00:22:48.450 --> 00:22:51.161
Hey! I'm a marine too!

483
00:22:51.661 --> 00:22:52.579
Oh.

484
00:22:52.662 --> 00:22:53.663
What class?

485
00:22:53.747 --> 00:22:56.041
Uh. I was in the 1.207th class.

486
00:22:58.293 --> 00:23:01.004
Sir! I was in the 1.216th class. sir!

487
00:23:01.088 --> 00:23:03.840
What are you doing? Sit. Please sit.

488
00:23:03.924 --> 00:23:05.604
I will sit when you return my salute. sir.

489
00:23:05.634 --> 00:23:06.927
Oh. uh...

490
00:23:10.639 --> 00:23:11.973
So you're Marine Kim Gun-woo.

491
00:23:12.057 --> 00:23:13.767
- Mm.
- So which division did you serve?

492
00:23:14.351 --> 00:23:15.227
The First Division.

493
00:23:15.310 --> 00:23:17.229
Me too! Which battalion were you in. sir?

494
00:23:18.438 --> 00:23:20.732
- Recon.
- Amazing.

495
00:23:21.400 --> 00:23:24.361
I also wanted to get into reconnaissance.
but I didn't make the cut.

496
00:23:24.444 --> 00:23:27.072
- Mm.
- The pride of the Marines. recon.

497
00:23:27.656 --> 00:23:29.324
Recon! [grunts]

498
00:23:29.825 --> 00:23:30.700
Ah!

499
00:23:30.784 --> 00:23:33.453
You can still call me "bro." okay?
Let's just speak casually.

500
00:23:34.496 --> 00:23:35.622
I understand. sir.

501
00:23:35.705 --> 00:23:36.998
Yeah. but let's be casual.

502
00:23:37.082 --> 00:23:38.542
Casual it is. sir.

503
00:23:38.625 --> 00:23:39.625
Bro.

504
00:23:39.668 --> 00:23:40.668
Hm?

505
00:23:41.044 --> 00:23:42.044
Here.

506
00:23:43.422 --> 00:23:44.881
[both laughing]

507
00:23:44.965 --> 00:23:49.219
Yeah. I have a crazy amount of pride
as a marine.

508
00:23:49.302 --> 00:23:50.137
Why?

509
00:23:50.220 --> 00:23:52.681
I was kind of a thug back in Incheon.

510
00:23:52.764 --> 00:23:53.964
but I joined the Marine Corps.

511
00:23:54.015 --> 00:23:55.735
met some nice people.
and came to my senses.

512
00:23:55.809 --> 00:23:57.060
I just loved it all.

513
00:23:57.144 --> 00:24:00.856
Going through tough training together
and overcoming it all.

514
00:24:00.939 --> 00:24:02.274
This looks delicious.

515
00:24:02.858 --> 00:24:05.360
Waking up in the morning.
going on runs. sweating bullets.

516
00:24:05.444 --> 00:24:06.987
then showering together.

517
00:24:07.070 --> 00:24:09.030
washing each. all that. you know.

518
00:24:09.948 --> 00:24:12.451
- You're one of those crazy marines?
- Of course not.

519
00:24:12.534 --> 00:24:13.702
You have to try this.

520
00:24:16.288 --> 00:24:17.288
How is it? How is it?

521
00:24:18.165 --> 00:24:19.165
[exhales]

522
00:24:19.708 --> 00:24:21.126
It's practically steak.

523
00:24:21.209 --> 00:24:23.086
Really? [laughs]

524
00:24:23.670 --> 00:24:24.754
Let me show you something.

525
00:24:26.006 --> 00:24:27.215
- Watch this.
- Wow. yes.

526
00:24:27.299 --> 00:24:29.299
- Three pieces with <i>ssamjang.</i>
- Yes. yes. yes. yes.

527
00:24:29.342 --> 00:24:30.677
Want some kimchi with that too?

528
00:24:33.805 --> 00:24:34.973
Ah. ah.

529
00:24:35.056 --> 00:24:37.017
- Marine Kim Gun-woo. sir.
- Yeah?

530
00:24:37.100 --> 00:24:38.435
- [grunts]
- [grunts]

531
00:24:40.353 --> 00:24:41.229
Mm. Mm.

532
00:24:41.313 --> 00:24:43.523
- Amazing. Amazing. right?
- Uh-huh. Mm-hm

533
00:24:43.607 --> 00:24:44.983
- Want to get some soju?
- No.

534
00:24:45.066 --> 00:24:46.943
- Why? Because of your diet?
- Mm-hm.

535
00:24:47.027 --> 00:24:48.445
You're such a perfectionist.

536
00:24:48.528 --> 00:24:50.280
You're too much. [laughs]

537
00:24:50.363 --> 00:24:51.363
Excuse me!

538
00:24:51.698 --> 00:24:52.616
A beer!

539
00:24:52.699 --> 00:24:55.744
Please. Ah!

540
00:24:57.412 --> 00:24:59.080
[Gun-woo] Bro. how much were your shoes?

541
00:24:59.581 --> 00:25:00.999
- 1.2 mill.
- Seriously?

542
00:25:01.500 --> 00:25:04.169
Why so expensive?
That's a month's rent for our store.

543
00:25:04.252 --> 00:25:05.795
Damn. you are really gullible.

544
00:25:05.879 --> 00:25:07.297
Obviously they're knockoffs.

545
00:25:08.924 --> 00:25:10.008
Well. they look real.

546
00:25:10.550 --> 00:25:12.302
Knockoffs have shiny toe caps. see?

547
00:25:12.385 --> 00:25:13.803
And the real ones are suede.

548
00:25:13.887 --> 00:25:15.931
The threads around the holes
are pretty shitty too.

549
00:25:16.932 --> 00:25:18.141
Tell me if you wanna buy some.

550
00:25:18.225 --> 00:25:19.827
I can get you better than the real thing.

551
00:25:19.851 --> 00:25:21.853
- Really?
- Are you shitting me? No. bro.

552
00:25:21.937 --> 00:25:25.106
There's nothing in the world
that tops the real deal. all right?

553
00:25:26.149 --> 00:25:28.920
You should hang out with me more.
so we can work on your street smarts.

554
00:25:28.944 --> 00:25:30.784
You spend too much time
on your part-time jobs.

555
00:25:31.279 --> 00:25:32.279
[Woo-jin grunts]

556
00:25:33.240 --> 00:25:36.326
Do you know about this?
I heard it's very common these days.

557
00:25:36.409 --> 00:25:38.912
[groans] "COVID-19 special loans."

558
00:25:38.995 --> 00:25:40.389
COVID-19 SUPPORT
SUPER LOW-INTEREST SPECIAL LOAN

559
00:25:40.413 --> 00:25:41.540
Back in the day.

560
00:25:41.623 --> 00:25:45.669
I was so strapped for cash.
that I worked in money lending.

561
00:25:45.752 --> 00:25:47.587
Desperate people are easier to rip off.

562
00:25:47.671 --> 00:25:49.965
The pandemic has made
many people desperate.

563
00:25:51.091 --> 00:25:52.091
[Woo-jin inhales deeply]

564
00:25:52.133 --> 00:25:54.970
So I guess now
all the loan sharks have come out to play.

565
00:25:55.053 --> 00:25:55.887
Really?

566
00:25:55.971 --> 00:25:58.807
Since everyone is rushing
to cover their rent.

567
00:25:58.890 --> 00:26:01.410
all the sharks need to do
is shake their hand and suck them dry.

568
00:26:03.270 --> 00:26:06.565
My mom is also having a hard time
because of the rent payments for her café.

569
00:26:07.190 --> 00:26:09.859
The business makes less than a fourth
of what we used to.

570
00:26:09.943 --> 00:26:12.023
but the landlord still takes
the same amount of rent.

571
00:26:13.613 --> 00:26:15.865
If we close down now.
it would cost us more to move out.

572
00:26:15.949 --> 00:26:17.826
so we're just trying to stay afloat.

573
00:26:17.909 --> 00:26:20.537
Apparently. you have to return the store
to its original state.

574
00:26:21.371 --> 00:26:22.622
[sighs] Damn.

575
00:26:26.793 --> 00:26:27.793
Here.

576
00:26:29.796 --> 00:26:32.257
I'll treat you
to something real fancy next time.

577
00:26:33.300 --> 00:26:35.427
- Are we gonna have rib eye?
- Ah. just come with me.

578
00:26:35.510 --> 00:26:36.970
I know a good barbecue place.

579
00:26:37.053 --> 00:26:38.305
You aren't messing with me?

580
00:26:38.388 --> 00:26:42.350
Hey. do you think I would tell
such a low-level lie to a senior marine?

581
00:26:42.434 --> 00:26:45.395
- [chuckles] I think you would.
- So you don't believe me?

582
00:26:45.478 --> 00:26:47.897
I just mean
because you've been lying to me all day.

583
00:26:47.981 --> 00:26:50.775
- [scoffs] Man. those were just jokes.
- [chuckles]

584
00:26:50.859 --> 00:26:52.569
All right. I promise no more lies.

585
00:26:53.862 --> 00:26:55.071
- Deal.
- [chuckles]

586
00:26:55.864 --> 00:26:57.115
[sighs] I know.

587
00:26:57.741 --> 00:26:59.075
I am so sorry.

588
00:26:59.159 --> 00:27:00.368
I tried my best.

589
00:27:00.952 --> 00:27:02.454
I just couldn't... [sighs]

590
00:27:03.121 --> 00:27:04.748
...get it together in time.

591
00:27:05.498 --> 00:27:09.794
Yes. if I just get through this month.
I will come up with it somehow.

592
00:27:10.962 --> 00:27:12.213
Again. I am sorry.

593
00:27:13.798 --> 00:27:15.050
Oh. uh. sorry.

594
00:27:15.133 --> 00:27:17.010
- Let me call you back in the morning.
- Mom!

595
00:27:18.136 --> 00:27:20.263
My boy! [laughs]

596
00:27:20.347 --> 00:27:21.931
Oh my boy!

597
00:27:22.015 --> 00:27:23.375
- [Gun-woo grunts]
- [woman laughs]

598
00:27:23.892 --> 00:27:25.852
Look at you. You were incredible today.

599
00:27:25.935 --> 00:27:28.146
- You watched it?
- Oh. of course I watched it.

600
00:27:28.229 --> 00:27:30.940
The commentators kept talking about you
the whole time.

601
00:27:31.024 --> 00:27:33.777
- Are you serious?
- Yes. they kept saying you're perfect.

602
00:27:33.860 --> 00:27:36.363
- So I guess I should watch it too then.
- [laughs]

603
00:27:36.446 --> 00:27:37.548
- Mom. hold on.
- Look at you.

604
00:27:37.572 --> 00:27:39.199
I'm so proud of you.

605
00:27:40.200 --> 00:27:41.326
[Gun-woo] Here. [exhales]

606
00:27:42.202 --> 00:27:43.202
What's that?

607
00:27:43.870 --> 00:27:45.997
The prize. so we can pay the rent.

608
00:27:48.333 --> 00:27:49.417
Oh.

609
00:27:50.001 --> 00:27:51.836
Oh. no. no. I can't take this.

610
00:27:53.505 --> 00:27:55.423
No. Mom. I won this to give it to you.

611
00:27:56.966 --> 00:27:58.218
[Gun-woo laughs softly]

612
00:27:58.885 --> 00:28:01.888
Let's pay... Uncle back first
for what we owe.

613
00:28:02.472 --> 00:28:03.472
[gasps]

614
00:28:04.683 --> 00:28:06.601
How... how do you know about your uncle?

615
00:28:06.685 --> 00:28:09.979
He's also going through a lot. Mom.
Let's pay him back.

616
00:28:11.231 --> 00:28:12.231
[exhales]

617
00:28:14.609 --> 00:28:15.609
All right.

618
00:28:16.569 --> 00:28:19.489
But listen. I will pay you back for this
with interest.

619
00:28:19.572 --> 00:28:23.034
- Okay.
- Oh. thank you.

620
00:28:26.287 --> 00:28:29.207
- Let's go. Mom.
- Ah. it's so cold. Let's go.

621
00:28:30.333 --> 00:28:31.333
Did you eat?

622
00:28:31.376 --> 00:28:32.376
Yeah. of course.

623
00:28:32.419 --> 00:28:33.795
Oh. with who?

624
00:28:34.379 --> 00:28:35.630
The guy I fought in the finals.

625
00:28:37.507 --> 00:28:40.802
Oh. the boy with the curly hair?

626
00:28:40.885 --> 00:28:41.885
Yeah. that one.

627
00:28:42.929 --> 00:28:44.973
- [laughs]
- Mom. did you eat?

628
00:28:45.056 --> 00:28:46.516
Oh. sure. sure. I ate.

629
00:28:49.519 --> 00:28:50.895
[tense music playing]

630
00:29:05.201 --> 00:29:06.201
Sir.

631
00:29:06.619 --> 00:29:07.619
How are things?

632
00:29:08.413 --> 00:29:09.706
Sir. as you predicted.

633
00:29:09.789 --> 00:29:12.834
all tenants owed money to banks
or second-tier financial companies.

634
00:29:13.585 --> 00:29:16.629
So my plan is to bring all of them to us
by next week.

635
00:29:16.713 --> 00:29:19.549
Okay. can you make it happen by this week?

636
00:29:20.175 --> 00:29:22.969
Assemblyman Seo keeps badgering me
to kick them out quickly.

637
00:29:23.720 --> 00:29:25.513
[chuckles] I'll see what I can do. sir.

638
00:29:25.597 --> 00:29:27.724
Yes. let's hurry things along.

639
00:29:28.266 --> 00:29:30.268
The sales team's operations are key.
aren't they?

640
00:29:31.060 --> 00:29:32.060
Yes. they are.

641
00:29:36.483 --> 00:29:37.567
Beom. listen.

642
00:29:39.652 --> 00:29:40.652
Let's get ready.

643
00:29:41.905 --> 00:29:43.615
[tense music continues]

644
00:30:00.215 --> 00:30:03.301
[woman] I am team manager Yoo In-yeong
from Smile Capital.

645
00:30:03.384 --> 00:30:05.345
We are a financial company

646
00:30:05.428 --> 00:30:07.806
that was recently government-certified
for excellence.

647
00:30:07.889 --> 00:30:11.226
and I was wondering
if you had some time for a quick chat.

648
00:30:11.309 --> 00:30:12.309
Okay.

649
00:30:12.727 --> 00:30:15.897
Your business doesn't get many visitors
these days. huh?

650
00:30:15.980 --> 00:30:16.980
[sighs]

651
00:30:17.398 --> 00:30:18.316
No.

652
00:30:18.399 --> 00:30:21.152
I believe you owe the bank 40 million won.
Is that accurate. sir?

653
00:30:21.778 --> 00:30:22.612
Yeah.

654
00:30:22.695 --> 00:30:26.074
[man] Once you sign here.
we will pay off that debt today.

655
00:30:27.158 --> 00:30:31.412
And we have an interest rate of 5%
which is way lower than the bank's 7%.

656
00:30:31.496 --> 00:30:34.415
Doesn't that end up leaving you
without any actual profit?

657
00:30:34.499 --> 00:30:35.416
[In-yeong] <i>That's true.</i>

658
00:30:35.500 --> 00:30:38.962
But. uh. the government has started
a special support project

659
00:30:39.045 --> 00:30:40.880
to help the small business owners

660
00:30:40.964 --> 00:30:43.091
who are struggling
because of the pandemic.

661
00:30:43.174 --> 00:30:44.175
We won a support package.

662
00:30:44.259 --> 00:30:47.196
which allows us to lower interest rates
even more than the other companies.

663
00:30:47.220 --> 00:30:50.098
A 2% difference in interest
is not a small amount

664
00:30:50.723 --> 00:30:53.768
In times like these.
just staying afloat is winning.

665
00:30:54.686 --> 00:30:57.188
- [exhales]
- We know this pandemic will pass soon.

666
00:30:57.272 --> 00:30:58.582
DEBT REPAYMENT
AND NEW CONTRACT AGREEMENT

667
00:30:58.606 --> 00:31:01.192
But we want to extend
whatever help we can.

668
00:31:01.276 --> 00:31:02.777
so that you can keep your business.

669
00:31:05.363 --> 00:31:07.031
It's true this is good for us too.

670
00:31:07.115 --> 00:31:09.325
but it's really good for you. sir.

671
00:31:12.370 --> 00:31:14.831
- Yes. thank you.
- Thank you so much. [laughs]

672
00:31:14.914 --> 00:31:16.332
SMILE CAPITAL
SIGNEE YOON SO-YEON

673
00:31:22.046 --> 00:31:23.046
[music ends]

674
00:31:29.846 --> 00:31:31.514
[puffing]

675
00:31:32.557 --> 00:31:33.557
Huh?

676
00:31:33.600 --> 00:31:35.077
TEMPORARILY CLOSED
DUE TO A CONFIRMED COVID-19 PATIENT

677
00:31:35.101 --> 00:31:38.897
We had dinner last night
with some of the other members at the gym.

678
00:31:38.980 --> 00:31:40.982
<i>Apparently. one of them tested positive.</i>

679
00:31:42.025 --> 00:31:44.402
Oh. do you think I should get tested too?

680
00:31:44.485 --> 00:31:45.486
[coach] <i>No. you're fine.</i>

681
00:31:45.570 --> 00:31:48.364
Anyway. your match was just yesterday.

682
00:31:48.448 --> 00:31:50.128
Why did I hear
that you're back at the gym?

683
00:31:50.158 --> 00:31:52.535
- To work out. Why else?
<i>- Gun-woo.</i>

684
00:31:53.119 --> 00:31:54.399
Please take a week off and rest.

685
00:31:54.954 --> 00:31:56.205
Rest doing what?

686
00:31:56.289 --> 00:31:58.917
Nothing. If you're doing something.
you're not resting.

687
00:31:59.000 --> 00:32:00.752
Just don't do anything and try to relax.

688
00:32:01.502 --> 00:32:02.502
Okay.

689
00:32:07.216 --> 00:32:08.217
[sighs]

690
00:32:09.135 --> 00:32:12.764
[cell phone ringing]

691
00:32:12.847 --> 00:32:15.183
GU-NOO

692
00:32:22.941 --> 00:32:24.525
Uh. what are you up to?

693
00:32:24.609 --> 00:32:26.235
[groans]

694
00:32:26.319 --> 00:32:27.528
Sleep.

695
00:32:27.612 --> 00:32:30.031
- Huh?
<i>- Sleeping.</i>

696
00:32:31.157 --> 00:32:33.576
- Uh. I can't hear you.
<i>- Sleep. sleeping.</i>

697
00:32:33.660 --> 00:32:35.954
I am sleeping.

698
00:32:36.621 --> 00:32:40.291
- Well. do you want to work out?
<i>- No.</i>

699
00:32:40.833 --> 00:32:42.126
Ah. but I'm bored.

700
00:32:42.210 --> 00:32:45.380
God. so clingy so early in the morning.

701
00:32:45.964 --> 00:32:47.298
Let's hang out. Hm?

702
00:32:48.007 --> 00:32:49.008
[sighs]

703
00:32:50.051 --> 00:32:52.720
I'll send my address. Come.

704
00:32:52.804 --> 00:32:54.597
[chuckles] Okay. sounds good.

705
00:33:10.989 --> 00:33:12.031
[man] Oh shit!

706
00:33:12.782 --> 00:33:14.617
[woman] Fuck! Goddammit. Stop!

707
00:33:15.201 --> 00:33:16.452
You son of a bitch!

708
00:33:18.663 --> 00:33:20.456
[dramatic music playing]

709
00:33:25.086 --> 00:33:26.921
[panting]

710
00:33:41.185 --> 00:33:42.311
[sighs]

711
00:33:45.314 --> 00:33:46.315
[man winces]

712
00:33:47.900 --> 00:33:49.110
[panting]

713
00:34:01.581 --> 00:34:04.042
- [hesitating] Are you all right?
- [man groans]

714
00:34:04.125 --> 00:34:05.251
Uh. okay. wait here.

715
00:34:05.334 --> 00:34:07.295
[tense music playing]

716
00:34:07.378 --> 00:34:09.380
[panting]

717
00:34:26.689 --> 00:34:28.566
- [music ends]
- [Gun-woo groans]

718
00:34:29.942 --> 00:34:31.486
[both panting]

719
00:34:32.695 --> 00:34:33.529
Who?

720
00:34:33.613 --> 00:34:34.613
Huh?

721
00:34:35.114 --> 00:34:36.449
Why'd you follow me?

722
00:34:37.116 --> 00:34:38.242
Tell me who sent you.

723
00:34:38.326 --> 00:34:39.827
[groaning]

724
00:34:39.911 --> 00:34:42.538
[sputtering] To help.

725
00:34:42.622 --> 00:34:44.957
What? Help who?

726
00:34:46.209 --> 00:34:48.836
[spluttering]
I thought that man was being chased.

727
00:34:48.920 --> 00:34:50.630
and. uh. I didn't know what was going on.

728
00:34:50.713 --> 00:34:52.840
- God fucking dammit.
- Huh?

729
00:34:52.924 --> 00:34:54.717
That asshole is a fake.

730
00:34:54.801 --> 00:34:57.220
- [Gun-woo] Huh?
- Just butt out of things you don't know.

731
00:34:57.303 --> 00:34:59.764
Motherfucker. [sighs]

732
00:35:04.894 --> 00:35:05.894
Huh?

733
00:35:06.854 --> 00:35:08.314
[grunts]

734
00:35:15.905 --> 00:35:16.906
[exhales deeply]

735
00:35:24.997 --> 00:35:27.542
[doorbell rings]

736
00:35:35.174 --> 00:35:36.092
What brings you here?

737
00:35:36.175 --> 00:35:38.010
Everything went well.

738
00:35:38.094 --> 00:35:40.138
I mean with Mi-yeon's surgery yesterday.

739
00:35:40.221 --> 00:35:42.390
Oh. really? And how is she doing now?

740
00:35:42.974 --> 00:35:44.016
She's good. sir.

741
00:35:44.100 --> 00:35:46.018
She's recovering very well.

742
00:35:47.353 --> 00:35:48.187
[exhales deeply]

743
00:35:48.271 --> 00:35:49.939
It's all thanks to you.

744
00:35:50.731 --> 00:35:52.692
If you hadn't helped us back then. sir.

745
00:35:53.192 --> 00:35:55.736
my daughter might have died.

746
00:35:57.488 --> 00:35:58.488
[man exhales]

747
00:35:59.323 --> 00:36:00.323
[woman] Here.

748
00:36:02.034 --> 00:36:05.121
My husband had the good fortune
of moving over to a larger company.

749
00:36:05.204 --> 00:36:07.373
so he just received his severance.

750
00:36:08.791 --> 00:36:11.043
I came here
as soon as the money hit our accounts

751
00:36:11.127 --> 00:36:14.130
because I wanted to pay you back
before I paid anyone else.

752
00:36:14.213 --> 00:36:15.256
[exhales]

753
00:36:17.508 --> 00:36:19.218
You can take your time to pay me back.

754
00:36:20.761 --> 00:36:22.263
First. pay back your urgent debts.

755
00:36:22.847 --> 00:36:23.848
Oh. no. sir.

756
00:36:23.931 --> 00:36:26.475
Please. Please accept this.

757
00:36:27.268 --> 00:36:29.437
I finally have some piece of mind.

758
00:36:30.146 --> 00:36:31.355
[sobbing]

759
00:36:32.398 --> 00:36:33.941
Thank you so much. sir.

760
00:36:35.818 --> 00:36:38.362
Thank you so much. Thank you so much.

761
00:36:38.863 --> 00:36:40.072
[breathes deeply]

762
00:36:41.073 --> 00:36:43.284
Thank you. [sobbing]

763
00:36:58.799 --> 00:37:00.927
MI-YEON'S MOTHER APRIL 14TH. 2018
20 MILLION WON

764
00:37:01.010 --> 00:37:02.595
[chuckles softly]

765
00:37:06.724 --> 00:37:12.772
KOREAN ANTIQUE MALL

766
00:37:30.623 --> 00:37:31.623
[door closes]

767
00:37:32.708 --> 00:37:34.126
I found Yang Jae-myeong.

768
00:37:34.210 --> 00:37:36.629
He tried telling me he had no money.

769
00:37:36.712 --> 00:37:38.005
so I took this from him.

770
00:37:42.051 --> 00:37:43.928
This watch goes for over 20 million won.

771
00:37:44.011 --> 00:37:45.054
So what?

772
00:37:45.972 --> 00:37:48.057
Yang Jae-myeong borrowed ten million won.

773
00:37:49.058 --> 00:37:50.518
Yeah. plus interest.

774
00:37:50.601 --> 00:37:51.601
[chuckles]

775
00:37:53.896 --> 00:37:54.897
[exhales deeply]

776
00:37:54.981 --> 00:37:56.124
- [groans]
- [joints cracking]

777
00:37:56.148 --> 00:37:57.191
Oh. did you get hurt?

778
00:37:57.275 --> 00:37:59.735
[exhales] I got in a scuffle
with Yang Jae-myeong.

779
00:38:00.736 --> 00:38:03.239
By the way.
while we're already on the subject.

780
00:38:03.322 --> 00:38:04.490
you and I need to talk.

781
00:38:04.573 --> 00:38:05.783
Have some rice cakes first.

782
00:38:06.701 --> 00:38:09.161
We need to talk.
Don't try to change the subject.

783
00:38:11.539 --> 00:38:13.019
How long are you going to keep at it?

784
00:38:14.417 --> 00:38:15.417
What?

785
00:38:17.295 --> 00:38:19.213
Lending people money with no interest.

786
00:38:19.297 --> 00:38:20.965
I mean. it's not profitable.

787
00:38:21.465 --> 00:38:22.550
What do you mean by that?

788
00:38:22.633 --> 00:38:25.845
I always pay you
your 30% in commission fees.

789
00:38:25.928 --> 00:38:28.097
Not for me. For you. Grandpa.

790
00:38:30.516 --> 00:38:31.516
[inhales]

791
00:38:32.018 --> 00:38:33.644
You know Mi-yeon's mother?

792
00:38:34.770 --> 00:38:35.771
Yeah. and?

793
00:38:35.855 --> 00:38:39.358
She dropped by earlier
and paid back the entire sum in cash.

794
00:38:41.277 --> 00:38:42.361
And that's the interest?

795
00:38:44.739 --> 00:38:45.739
Hyeon-ju.

796
00:38:46.240 --> 00:38:48.909
A sick child got a timely operation
that saved her.

797
00:38:48.993 --> 00:38:50.536
Because I lent them money.

798
00:38:50.619 --> 00:38:53.664
her parents didn't have to use their home
as collateral for a loan.

799
00:38:53.748 --> 00:38:57.168
And now. when their child's better.
she has a home to go to.

800
00:38:58.586 --> 00:39:00.296
You and I saved a family.

801
00:39:01.339 --> 00:39:04.091
This is the most precious form of interest
in the world.

802
00:39:05.885 --> 00:39:06.885
[sighs]

803
00:39:07.720 --> 00:39:09.847
Well. anyway. I heard something

804
00:39:09.930 --> 00:39:12.090
while digging around
for Yang Jae-myeong's whereabouts.

805
00:39:12.892 --> 00:39:15.394
He and his crew are dressing up
as homeless people

806
00:39:15.478 --> 00:39:18.022
and robbing the actual homeless
of their IDs

807
00:39:18.105 --> 00:39:19.416
to take out loans in their names.

808
00:39:19.440 --> 00:39:21.067
And who are these people?

809
00:39:21.150 --> 00:39:23.319
They're not exactly the cream of the crop.

810
00:39:23.402 --> 00:39:24.403
They met in prison.

811
00:39:24.487 --> 00:39:26.447
You knew this.
and you went all by yourself?

812
00:39:27.323 --> 00:39:28.991
Should I have you tag along next time?

813
00:39:29.075 --> 00:39:31.786
- [inhales sharply]
- Anyway. let me do some digging.

814
00:39:32.453 --> 00:39:34.133
I think I will find something interesting.

815
00:39:34.163 --> 00:39:35.998
As long as you're not in danger. okay?

816
00:39:36.582 --> 00:39:37.582
Sure.

817
00:39:47.426 --> 00:39:50.471
PRESIDENT MOON GWANG-MU

818
00:39:50.554 --> 00:39:52.681
MARINE
IF IT DOESN'T WORK. MAKE IT WORK!

819
00:39:52.765 --> 00:39:53.599
Hello?

820
00:39:53.682 --> 00:39:56.477
Hi. Oh. is this a bad time?

821
00:39:56.560 --> 00:39:57.770
No. sir. No. please go ahead.

822
00:39:57.853 --> 00:40:00.856
Yes. I wanted to ask you a favor
to find someone.

823
00:40:00.940 --> 00:40:02.024
One second. please.

824
00:40:03.818 --> 00:40:04.819
All right. I'm listening.

825
00:40:05.903 --> 00:40:06.904
"A good person."

826
00:40:08.197 --> 00:40:09.657
"A skilled bodyguard

827
00:40:10.741 --> 00:40:13.285
who is familiar with the loan business."

828
00:40:16.539 --> 00:40:17.748
All right. sir.

829
00:40:18.249 --> 00:40:20.835
I will find the best candidates.
I promise I will find the best.

830
00:40:21.419 --> 00:40:22.753
I'll leave it in your hands.

831
00:40:22.837 --> 00:40:24.797
Yes. sir. Anytime.

832
00:40:26.715 --> 00:40:29.051
Mayweather is the top dog. No doubt.

833
00:40:29.135 --> 00:40:31.303
But Mayweather feels
more like a businessman

834
00:40:31.387 --> 00:40:32.471
than an actual boxer.

835
00:40:32.555 --> 00:40:33.389
That's right.

836
00:40:33.472 --> 00:40:36.434
My guy's in it for the money.
but he is ridiculously good at it.

837
00:40:37.143 --> 00:40:38.978
Probably made a few hundred billion.

838
00:40:39.520 --> 00:40:40.771
Does money matter to you?

839
00:40:41.897 --> 00:40:43.357
What could matter more than money?

840
00:40:44.066 --> 00:40:45.192
The heart of a boxer.

841
00:40:46.527 --> 00:40:47.528
[chuckles]

842
00:40:48.320 --> 00:40:49.196
What?

843
00:40:49.280 --> 00:40:51.282
[laughing]

844
00:40:51.866 --> 00:40:54.076
- What?
- [cackling]

845
00:40:55.995 --> 00:40:58.873
- Dude.
- No. No. Sorry.

846
00:41:00.082 --> 00:41:02.001
It's just you got so serious
all of a sudden.

847
00:41:02.084 --> 00:41:04.545
You looked so serious
that it really caught me off guard.

848
00:41:05.045 --> 00:41:06.881
Elaborate on this boxer's heart.

849
00:41:07.465 --> 00:41:08.465
Hm.

850
00:41:09.592 --> 00:41:11.927
I think Manny Pacquiao
is the best example because...

851
00:41:12.011 --> 00:41:15.306
Pow! Pow. pow. Pacquiao! Pow. pow.

852
00:41:15.389 --> 00:41:18.642
Come on. dude. Let me have my moment.
I never cut you off. man.

853
00:41:19.393 --> 00:41:22.605
I'm sorry. marine.
I will never cut you off. [grunts]

854
00:41:22.688 --> 00:41:26.942
Well. I really admire Pacquiao's heart.
you know? He never gives up.

855
00:41:27.026 --> 00:41:30.738
Okay. I can give him that.
but Mayweather made a lot more money.

856
00:41:30.821 --> 00:41:34.658
But I bet a lot more kids started dreaming
of becoming a boxer because of Pacquiao.

857
00:41:34.742 --> 00:41:36.160
That's true for me at least.

858
00:41:37.620 --> 00:41:40.539
That's the kind of person I want to be.

859
00:41:40.623 --> 00:41:44.168
A person who shows
that with strong will and undying passion.

860
00:41:44.251 --> 00:41:46.251
anyone will be able to achieve
all of their dreams.

861
00:41:46.295 --> 00:41:47.796
It's windy today.

862
00:41:47.880 --> 00:41:49.965
That is a true boxer's heart

863
00:41:50.049 --> 00:41:53.594
and the kind of hope we should inspire
in the people watching us.

864
00:41:54.512 --> 00:41:56.152
- A boxer's heart...
- Hey. this is ready.

865
00:41:56.222 --> 00:41:57.222
Let's eat.

866
00:41:57.264 --> 00:41:58.474
[inhales sharply]

867
00:41:59.350 --> 00:42:00.350
Here.

868
00:42:05.689 --> 00:42:07.399
- Is it good?
- So good.

869
00:42:08.734 --> 00:42:10.819
Hey. what do you do for a living?

870
00:42:10.903 --> 00:42:14.907
I used to teach gym classes
at a kindergarten my friend runs.

871
00:42:14.990 --> 00:42:16.492
[sniffles] A gym teacher of sorts.

872
00:42:17.034 --> 00:42:18.536
Ah. that doesn't suit you. right?

873
00:42:18.619 --> 00:42:19.828
What do you mean?

874
00:42:20.663 --> 00:42:21.830
Kids fucking love me.

875
00:42:22.414 --> 00:42:24.375
Well. anyway.
I used to do that in the morning.

876
00:42:24.458 --> 00:42:26.001
then worked out in the afternoons.

877
00:42:26.085 --> 00:42:27.965
Since the kindergarten shut down.
I'm in a bind.

878
00:42:30.297 --> 00:42:32.258
Hey. wanna go on deliveries with me?

879
00:42:32.341 --> 00:42:34.181
You can make some serious money
on parcel runs.

880
00:42:35.135 --> 00:42:36.637
- Is the pay good?
- Yeah.

881
00:42:36.720 --> 00:42:38.305
If we put our minds to it.

882
00:42:38.389 --> 00:42:40.766
we could probably make 200.000 each.

883
00:42:40.849 --> 00:42:41.725
For real?

884
00:42:41.809 --> 00:42:43.811
Yeah. delivery work is also good cardio.

885
00:42:43.894 --> 00:42:45.734
And you get to work on
your non-boxing muscles.

886
00:42:45.813 --> 00:42:47.173
so it's good for your balance too.

887
00:42:47.231 --> 00:42:50.651
- Ah. killing two birds with one stone.
- Three birds.

888
00:42:50.734 --> 00:42:51.569
Huh?

889
00:42:51.652 --> 00:42:54.572
You make money. get your cardio in.
and work on your balance.

890
00:42:54.655 --> 00:42:57.157
Yeah. cardio and balance are the same.

891
00:42:57.241 --> 00:42:58.993
Uh. no. they're not.

892
00:42:59.076 --> 00:43:00.494
[Woo-jin scoffs. clicks tongue]

893
00:43:00.995 --> 00:43:04.415
Wait. but aren't you supposed to compete
in the Super Series

894
00:43:04.498 --> 00:43:06.378
since you won
the Rookie of the Year tournament?

895
00:43:06.875 --> 00:43:09.795
Mm-hm. but it's been postposed
due to COVID.

896
00:43:12.298 --> 00:43:14.592
[sighs] How much longer?

897
00:43:15.301 --> 00:43:16.552
There's nothing I can do.

898
00:43:17.177 --> 00:43:18.177
[clicks tongue]

899
00:43:19.388 --> 00:43:23.142
Except I'll make sure I'm ready to fight
whenever the time actually comes.

900
00:43:26.186 --> 00:43:29.690
You know... you have a boxer's heart.

901
00:43:32.276 --> 00:43:34.361
[both laughing]

902
00:43:35.863 --> 00:43:38.407
- [Woo-jin puffing]
- Hm?

903
00:43:38.490 --> 00:43:40.367
- Come on. Pacquiao.
- Right now?

904
00:43:41.577 --> 00:43:42.577
[grunts]

905
00:43:46.165 --> 00:43:47.165
[Woo-jin groans]

906
00:43:47.207 --> 00:43:48.207
Whoa...

907
00:43:49.251 --> 00:43:50.711
Man. how could you hit me for real?

908
00:43:50.794 --> 00:43:52.004
Whoa. my bad. Sorry.

909
00:43:52.087 --> 00:43:53.567
Hey. come here. come here. Come here.

910
00:43:53.631 --> 00:43:54.715
Let go. Let go.

911
00:43:54.798 --> 00:43:57.885
- Come here. Let go. Come here. Come here.
- Whoa! Whoa!

912
00:43:57.968 --> 00:44:00.095
- Come here. Hey. Kim Gun-woo!
- [laughing]

913
00:44:00.971 --> 00:44:04.224
- [laughs] Everyone. cheers!
- [all cheering]

914
00:44:04.308 --> 00:44:07.603
- [electronic dance music playing]
- [all yelling]

915
00:44:07.686 --> 00:44:10.939
Now for today's main event.
The greatest show on Earth!

916
00:44:11.023 --> 00:44:13.817
- Cracking a watermelon with In-beom!
- [all cheering]

917
00:44:13.901 --> 00:44:17.112
Everyone. come on! Make your bets now!

918
00:44:17.196 --> 00:44:18.489
A million that he fails!

919
00:44:19.406 --> 00:44:23.243
Hey! Three million on his success.

920
00:44:24.078 --> 00:44:27.623
And if I'm the winner of this pot.
everything is on me!

921
00:44:27.706 --> 00:44:29.309
[Myeong-gil] Beom.
I know you can crack it.

922
00:44:29.333 --> 00:44:31.669
but I'm gonna bet four million
that you can't

923
00:44:31.752 --> 00:44:33.754
[all cheering]

924
00:44:33.837 --> 00:44:36.423
- [Jang-do chanting] Kang In-beom!
- [woman] Let's go!

925
00:44:36.507 --> 00:44:39.134
- Kang In-beom!
- Kang In-beom!

926
00:44:39.218 --> 00:44:41.178
- [yelling]
- Kang In-beom!

927
00:44:41.261 --> 00:44:43.013
- [In-beom grunts]
- [all cheering]

928
00:44:43.097 --> 00:44:43.972
He cracked it!

929
00:44:44.056 --> 00:44:45.933
[laughing]

930
00:44:46.016 --> 00:44:47.768
<i>Tteokbokki for all! Yeah!</i>

931
00:44:47.851 --> 00:44:49.645
Let's have some tteokbokki!

932
00:44:49.728 --> 00:44:50.813
Awesome job!

933
00:44:50.896 --> 00:44:51.814
Woo!

934
00:44:51.897 --> 00:44:53.315
I did well. didn't I?

935
00:44:53.399 --> 00:44:54.650
DEAREST MAYOR

936
00:44:56.902 --> 00:44:58.570
Shh. Quiet. Quiet!

937
00:44:58.654 --> 00:45:00.072
[cell phone ringing]

938
00:45:00.155 --> 00:45:01.532
[man clears throat]

939
00:45:05.119 --> 00:45:06.120
Yes. Mr. Mayor.

940
00:45:08.497 --> 00:45:09.832
- Yes.
- [inaudible dialogue]

941
00:45:12.626 --> 00:45:13.627
Yes.

942
00:45:17.673 --> 00:45:18.674
Yes.

943
00:45:20.175 --> 00:45:21.385
I understand. sir.

944
00:45:21.468 --> 00:45:22.761
I will let him know.

945
00:45:23.887 --> 00:45:25.222
Have a good evening. sir.

946
00:45:29.101 --> 00:45:31.770
The mayor... has just decided that

947
00:45:33.522 --> 00:45:34.690
he will back the casino bid.

948
00:45:35.524 --> 00:45:37.401
- Yes.
- Yes!

949
00:45:41.655 --> 00:45:43.073
[ominous music playing]

950
00:45:43.157 --> 00:45:48.996
I have prepared... a small gift for you.
Mr. Park. in honor of your birthday.

951
00:45:54.543 --> 00:45:55.543
Open it.

952
00:46:00.090 --> 00:46:01.884
[suspenseful music playing]

953
00:46:01.967 --> 00:46:03.594
Almost four kilos.

954
00:46:04.678 --> 00:46:09.683
Mr. Park. these gold turtles are so clean
that no one will know if you have them.

955
00:46:10.768 --> 00:46:12.269
I give you this with the hope

956
00:46:12.352 --> 00:46:15.272
that our relationship will continue
for a long time.

957
00:46:15.355 --> 00:46:18.692
So I would appreciate if you take them.

958
00:46:27.493 --> 00:46:29.870
You don't want to be in City Hall forever.

959
00:46:31.538 --> 00:46:33.415
I know you have big dreams. Mr. Park.

960
00:46:33.499 --> 00:46:36.502
If you plan on going
to the National Assembly.

961
00:46:36.585 --> 00:46:38.170
you will definitely need money.

962
00:46:39.129 --> 00:46:40.881
Let us forge a lasting partnership.

963
00:46:41.381 --> 00:46:43.759
I will support you every way I can.

964
00:46:45.427 --> 00:46:48.889
My money never has known failure.
You can rest assured.

965
00:46:50.015 --> 00:46:51.015
[grunts]

966
00:47:02.986 --> 00:47:05.864
- [slurring] Hey. Hey!
- [man] Jeez.

967
00:47:06.365 --> 00:47:08.367
Hey. where are we going?

968
00:47:08.450 --> 00:47:10.953
[man] Please get in carefully.
We'll take you home.

969
00:47:11.036 --> 00:47:12.496
[Mr. Park] Let's go. [grunts]

970
00:47:13.997 --> 00:47:14.997
[groans]

971
00:47:18.460 --> 00:47:20.337
And Assemblyman Seo's building?

972
00:47:21.088 --> 00:47:22.798
Just wait until Friday. sir.

973
00:47:23.507 --> 00:47:26.134
All the stores will have
over 20 million in interest.

974
00:47:26.635 --> 00:47:28.679
I think the small stores
need a little grilling.

975
00:47:29.179 --> 00:47:31.139
People tend to give up faster

976
00:47:31.223 --> 00:47:34.268
if they see their first-floor storefront
in complete shambles

977
00:47:34.351 --> 00:47:36.436
every time they come into work. you know?

978
00:47:38.272 --> 00:47:39.523
I'll do as you wish. sir.

979
00:47:39.606 --> 00:47:40.732
[Myeong-gil inhales sharply]

980
00:47:40.816 --> 00:47:43.485
Since Mr. Jung is not feeling well
and can't join you.

981
00:47:43.569 --> 00:47:46.446
call them and tell them to send over
15 intimidating men.

982
00:47:46.530 --> 00:47:47.990
Beom can wrap things up.

983
00:47:48.073 --> 00:47:49.533
Should they be armed?

984
00:47:50.117 --> 00:47:51.159
There's no need.

985
00:47:51.243 --> 00:47:54.162
Tell them to suit up
and make sure that everyone is masked.

986
00:47:54.246 --> 00:47:56.415
Sir. I think five men should be enough.

987
00:47:56.498 --> 00:47:59.459
I'm sure that the boss has his reasons.

988
00:48:01.461 --> 00:48:02.713
You're right.

989
00:48:03.338 --> 00:48:04.590
I've made a huge mistake.

990
00:48:05.090 --> 00:48:07.467
[both laughing]

991
00:48:07.551 --> 00:48:09.553
You shitheads. there you go again.

992
00:48:09.636 --> 00:48:11.430
Come on. Focus.

993
00:48:12.764 --> 00:48:13.891
Where should we begin?

994
00:48:15.601 --> 00:48:16.894
[exhales]

995
00:48:22.065 --> 00:48:23.609
[tense music playing]

996
00:48:45.213 --> 00:48:46.213
[music ends]

997
00:48:46.965 --> 00:48:48.133
[bell ringing]

998
00:48:51.219 --> 00:48:52.219
[So-yeon] Huh?

999
00:48:52.846 --> 00:48:54.848
Oh. hello. Good evening.

1000
00:48:55.891 --> 00:48:57.211
Why didn't you keep your promise?

1001
00:48:58.810 --> 00:48:59.645
What?

1002
00:48:59.728 --> 00:49:01.480
You agreed to an extension fee

1003
00:49:02.773 --> 00:49:04.608
in exchange for a lowered interest rate.

1004
00:49:05.192 --> 00:49:06.360
Uh. what?

1005
00:49:07.819 --> 00:49:12.658
But you needed to pay that extension fee.
which is 10% of the principal.

1006
00:49:13.241 --> 00:49:14.868
within 24 hours of signing.

1007
00:49:14.952 --> 00:49:16.787
- It says so on the contract.
- [gasps]

1008
00:49:16.870 --> 00:49:18.914
But because you failed to do so.

1009
00:49:19.790 --> 00:49:22.417
your extension
has accrued 40 million in interest.

1010
00:49:22.501 --> 00:49:24.261
Not to mention
your credit score has dropped.

1011
00:49:24.294 --> 00:49:26.672
so your interest rate has gone up to 20%.

1012
00:49:27.297 --> 00:49:32.135
We really... started
with the purest of intentions.

1013
00:49:32.219 --> 00:49:33.261
[laughs]

1014
00:49:33.345 --> 00:49:35.347
- You ruined everything. damn it!
- [gasps]

1015
00:49:35.430 --> 00:49:36.807
[panting]

1016
00:49:37.641 --> 00:49:39.101
What are you going to do now?

1017
00:49:40.102 --> 00:49:41.520
Do you have that kind of money?

1018
00:49:45.232 --> 00:49:46.650
I will call the police.

1019
00:49:47.567 --> 00:49:48.567
Police?

1020
00:49:50.153 --> 00:49:51.154
Yeah.

1021
00:50:00.956 --> 00:50:02.708
[panting]

1022
00:50:02.791 --> 00:50:03.959
Oh my God.

1023
00:50:06.670 --> 00:50:07.796
[phone line ringing]

1024
00:50:11.133 --> 00:50:12.259
[Gun-woo] <i>Hey. Mom.</i>

1025
00:50:12.342 --> 00:50:13.885
Hey. son. where are you?

1026
00:50:13.969 --> 00:50:17.389
- I'm almost there.
<i>- Okay. I'm at the store.</i>

1027
00:50:17.472 --> 00:50:19.558
<i>And a bunch of strange people came over...</i>

1028
00:50:19.641 --> 00:50:21.435
Strange people? Who?

1029
00:50:21.518 --> 00:50:22.602
They're still here.

1030
00:50:23.562 --> 00:50:26.189
- [screaming]
- Mom? What's going on?

1031
00:50:26.273 --> 00:50:27.441
[screaming]

1032
00:50:33.822 --> 00:50:34.906
[tense music playing]

1033
00:50:34.990 --> 00:50:37.659
[car horns honking]

1034
00:50:40.287 --> 00:50:41.287
[grunts]

1035
00:50:41.997 --> 00:50:44.124
- [man grunting]
- [whimpering]

1036
00:50:47.419 --> 00:50:48.420
[music intensifying]

1037
00:50:48.920 --> 00:50:49.920
[grunts]

1038
00:50:57.596 --> 00:50:58.638
[Gun-woo panting]

1039
00:50:59.181 --> 00:51:01.183
[man 1] Where the hell
do you think you're going?

1040
00:51:01.266 --> 00:51:04.019
Who the hell are you? Get lost!

1041
00:51:05.103 --> 00:51:07.272
Hey! I told you to scram. asshole!

1042
00:51:07.856 --> 00:51:08.856
[So-yeon grunts]

1043
00:51:09.691 --> 00:51:11.359
This jackass! Hey. you!

1044
00:51:11.443 --> 00:51:13.070
[Gun-woo grunting]

1045
00:51:13.153 --> 00:51:15.381
- [man 2] What's going on? Get him.
- [man 3] You shithead!

1046
00:51:15.405 --> 00:51:17.074
[man 2] Who the hell is this guy?

1047
00:51:19.367 --> 00:51:21.203
[panting]

1048
00:51:23.663 --> 00:51:24.706
[rock music playing]

1049
00:51:24.790 --> 00:51:26.625
[grunting]

1050
00:51:30.212 --> 00:51:31.088
[man 5] Fuck!

1051
00:51:31.171 --> 00:51:32.339
[grunts]

1052
00:51:32.422 --> 00:51:34.102
- [man 6] Come here.
- [man 5] Little shit!

1053
00:51:38.095 --> 00:51:40.514
[grunting]

1054
00:52:01.451 --> 00:52:02.731
- [Gun-woo grunting]
- [coughing]

1055
00:52:18.510 --> 00:52:20.053
- [shouts]
- [rock music ends]

1056
00:52:21.054 --> 00:52:22.054
[men groaning]

1057
00:52:22.097 --> 00:52:23.640
[So-yeon groaning]

1058
00:52:23.723 --> 00:52:25.058
[So-yeon whimpering]

1059
00:52:25.142 --> 00:52:27.519
- Mom. are you all right?
- Yes.

1060
00:52:27.602 --> 00:52:28.645
You aren't hurt. are you?

1061
00:52:28.728 --> 00:52:31.481
- [sobbing] I'm okay. I'm okay.
- [panting]

1062
00:52:41.449 --> 00:52:42.449
Who are you?

1063
00:52:43.827 --> 00:52:46.454
- Who are you to do this to our store?
- [grunts]

1064
00:52:47.789 --> 00:52:49.666
- I asked you. "Who are you?"
- [grunts]

1065
00:52:52.711 --> 00:52:54.671
- [chuckling]
- [ominous music playing]

1066
00:53:04.306 --> 00:53:06.308
[So-yeon breathing deeply]

1067
00:53:09.102 --> 00:53:10.437
[Myeong-gil] Calm down. kid.

1068
00:53:11.396 --> 00:53:14.691
Your mother has borrowed some money
from our company.

1069
00:53:15.275 --> 00:53:17.569
- [panting]
- Mm-hm

1070
00:53:19.237 --> 00:53:20.405
So what do you want?

1071
00:53:21.698 --> 00:53:22.908
Pay us back.

1072
00:53:23.575 --> 00:53:25.327
Pay us for the damages first.

1073
00:53:31.958 --> 00:53:33.960
[So-yeon whimpering]

1074
00:53:44.554 --> 00:53:45.554
[scoffs]

1075
00:53:47.098 --> 00:53:48.183
Go ahead.

1076
00:53:53.772 --> 00:53:54.898
[grunts]

1077
00:53:59.486 --> 00:54:01.863
Mom. it's okay.
Just go over there for a second.

1078
00:54:01.947 --> 00:54:03.907
[So-yeon] Gun-woo! [whimpers]

1079
00:54:03.990 --> 00:54:05.367
[sobbing]

1080
00:54:10.830 --> 00:54:12.791
[music building]

1081
00:54:15.252 --> 00:54:16.252
[Gun-woo grunting]

1082
00:54:17.545 --> 00:54:19.172
[growls]

1083
00:54:23.677 --> 00:54:24.677
[Gun-woo grunts]

1084
00:54:26.513 --> 00:54:27.639
[Gun-woo grunts]

1085
00:54:33.270 --> 00:54:34.354
[exhales]

1086
00:54:36.940 --> 00:54:41.569
[grunting]

1087
00:54:45.031 --> 00:54:46.491
- [In-beom grunts]
- [Gun-woo groans]

1088
00:54:46.574 --> 00:54:47.575
[So-yeon screams]

1089
00:54:48.618 --> 00:54:50.620
[In-beom grunting]

1090
00:55:00.964 --> 00:55:01.964
[grunts]

1091
00:55:02.632 --> 00:55:03.633
[grunts]

1092
00:55:05.969 --> 00:55:06.969
[grunts]

1093
00:55:12.350 --> 00:55:13.518
[sobbing]

1094
00:55:18.356 --> 00:55:19.441
[grunts]

1095
00:55:20.191 --> 00:55:21.609
[So-yeon] Gun-woo!

1096
00:55:22.610 --> 00:55:23.611
[Gun-woo grunts]

1097
00:55:23.695 --> 00:55:24.779
[panting]

1098
00:55:27.866 --> 00:55:29.951
[grunting]

1099
00:55:39.336 --> 00:55:40.503
[screams]

1100
00:55:44.049 --> 00:55:45.050
[shouts]

1101
00:55:47.969 --> 00:55:49.929
[In-beom grunting]

1102
00:55:50.013 --> 00:55:51.848
Gun-woo!

1103
00:55:53.350 --> 00:55:54.434
[grunts]

1104
00:55:58.438 --> 00:55:59.439
[gurgles blood]

1105
00:56:00.565 --> 00:56:01.565
[So-yeon screams]

1106
00:56:10.241 --> 00:56:11.241
That's enough.

1107
00:56:20.752 --> 00:56:21.752
[Myeong-gil sighs]

1108
00:56:26.174 --> 00:56:27.717
[coughing]

1109
00:56:28.802 --> 00:56:30.261
[So-yeon sobbing]

1110
00:56:32.305 --> 00:56:34.933
[breathing heavily]

1111
00:56:35.016 --> 00:56:38.978
Hey. I appreciate people with grit.

1112
00:56:40.855 --> 00:56:44.442
Because guys with grit...
They can get anything done.

1113
00:56:47.695 --> 00:56:49.280
Do you want to work for me?

1114
00:56:49.364 --> 00:56:50.865
I will make sure that...

1115
00:56:51.699 --> 00:56:52.951
[coughing]

1116
00:56:55.120 --> 00:56:57.497
- [Gun-woo coughing]
- [scoffs]

1117
00:57:03.044 --> 00:57:04.129
[Gun-woo gasps]

1118
00:57:07.215 --> 00:57:08.466
[screams]

1119
00:57:09.300 --> 00:57:10.300
[grunts]

1120
00:57:10.927 --> 00:57:12.762
[So-yeon wailing]

1121
00:57:22.355 --> 00:57:25.608
- [Myeong-gil grunts]
- [grunting]

1122
00:57:28.027 --> 00:57:29.027
[grunts]

1123
00:57:30.029 --> 00:57:32.866
[yelling]

1124
00:57:36.744 --> 00:57:38.830
[laughing sinisterly]

1125
00:57:43.209 --> 00:57:44.878
[theme music playing]

1126
00:59:32.527 --> 00:59:33.695
[theme music ends]

